bob/backend/README.md", "content": "# Kalshi Trading System — Backend\\n\\nA ful
l-stack trading infrastructure for Kalshi prediction markets. Fetches live marke
t data, generates trading signals via multiple strategies, manages risk, and exe
cutes paper trades.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Quick Start (15 Minutes)\\n\\n### 1. Instal
l Dependencies\\n\\n```bash\\ncd agents/bob/backend\\nnpm install\\n```\\n\\n###
2. Set Environment Variables\\n\\n```bash\\nexport KALSHI_API_KEY=\\"your_api_ke
y_here\\"  # Optional: uses mock data if not set\\nexport KALSHI_DEMO=\\"true\\"
thout `KALSHI_API_KEY`, the system runs in mock mode with realistic synthetic ma
rket data.\\n\\n### 3. Run the Trading Pipeline\\n\\n```bash\\n# Generate signal
s (dry run - no trades executed)\\nnode strategies/live_runner.js\\n\\n# Execute
paper trades\\nnode strategies/live_runner.js --execute\\n```\\n\\nOutput: `agen
ts/bob/output/trade_signals.json`\\n\\n### 4. Start the Dashboard\\n\\n```bash\\
n# Terminal 1: Start the API server\\nnode dashboard_api.js\\n\\n# Terminal 2: O
pen the dashboard\\nopen dashboard/index.html\\n# Or visit: http://localhost:320
0 (if serving via API)\\n```\\n\\nThe dashboard auto-refreshes every 60 seconds.
\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Architecture Overview\\n\\n```\\n┌─────────────────┐     ┌────
─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\\n│  Data Fetcher   │────▶│   Strategies 
  │────▶│  Risk Manager   │\\n│  (kalshi_client)│     │  (signal_engine)│     │ 
(risk_manager) │\\n└─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └────────────
─────┘\\n         │                       │                       │\\n         ▼
────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\\n│  Market Data    │     │  Trade Signals
 │────▶│  Execution      │\\n│  (trade_signals)│     │  (position_sizer)│    │  
(execution_engine)│\\n└─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └─────────
────────┘\\n         │                       │                       │\\n       
 └───────────────────────┼───────────────────────┘\\n                           
   Dashboard    │\\n                        │  (dashboard_api)│\\n              
\\n\\n### Components\\n\\n| Component | File | Purpose |\\n|-----------|------|-
--------|\\n| **Kalshi Client** | `kalshi_client.js` | Authenticated API client 
for market data |\\n| **Signal Engine** | `strategies/signal_engine.js` | Scans 
markets, generates signals |\\n| **Position Sizer** | `strategies/position_sizer
.js` | Kelly criterion + fixed fractional sizing |\\n| **Risk Manager** | `strat
egies/risk_manager.js` | Daily loss limits, exposure caps |\\n| **Execution Engi
ne** | `strategies/execution_engine.js` | Order submission, fill tracking |\\n| 
**Live Runner** | `strategies/live_runner.js` | Orchestrates the full pipeline |
\\n| **Dashboard API** | `dashboard_api.js` | Express server on port 3200 |\\n| 
**Dashboard UI** | `dashboard/index.html` | Real-time trading dashboard |\\n\\n#
## Strategies\\n\\n| Strategy | File | Description |\\n|----------|------|------
-------|\\n| Mean Reversion | `strategies/strategies/mean_reversion.js` | Z-scor
e based reversion to mean |\\n| Momentum | `strategies/strategies/momentum.js` |
Price momentum + volume |\\n| Crypto Edge | `strategies/strategies/crypto_edge.j
s` | Lognormal model vs market price |\\n| NFP Nowcast | `strategies/strategies/
nfp_nowcast.js` | Non-farm payroll predictions |\\n| Econ Edge | `strategies/str
ategies/econ_edge.js` | Economic indicator edges |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Environment 
Variables\\n\\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\\n|----------|---
-------|---------|-------------|\\n| `KALSHI_API_KEY` | No | — | Kalshi API key 
for live data |\\n| `KALSHI_DEMO` | No | `true` | Use demo environment |\\n| `PO
RT` | No | `3200` | Dashboard API port |\\n| `DB_HOST` | No | `localhost` | Post
greSQL host |\\n| `DB_PORT` | No | `5432` | PostgreSQL port |\\n| `DB_NAME` | No
| `kalshi` | Database name |\\n| `DB_USER` | No | — | Database user |\\n| `DB_PA
SS` | No | — | Database password |\\n\\n### Example `.env` File\\n\\n```bash\\n#
Copy to .env and fill in your values\\nKALSHI_API_KEY=kalshi_demo_xxxxxxxx\\nKAL
SHI_DEMO=true\\nPORT=3200\\n\\nDB_HOST=localhost\\nDB_PORT=5432\\nDB_NAME=kalshi
\\nDB_USER=trader\\nDB_PASS=secret\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Running Backtests\\n\\
n```bash\\n# Run all strategy backtests\\nnode strategies/backtest.js\\n\\n# Run
specific strategy\\nnode strategies/backtest.js --strategy=mean_reversion\\n\\n#
Run with custom date range\\nnode strategies/backtest.js --start=2026-01-01 --en
d=2026-03-31\\n```\\n\\nOutput: `agents/bob/output/backtest_results.json`\\n\\n-
--\\n\\n## Dashboard\\n\\nThe dashboard provides real-time visibility into the t
rading system.\\n\\n### Opening the Dashboard\\n\\n```bash\\n# Method 1: Direct 
file open\\nopen dashboard/index.html\\n\\n# Method 2: Via API server (serves on
port 3200)\\nnode dashboard_api.js\\n# Then visit: http://localhost:3200\\n```\\
n\\n### Dashboard Features\\n\\n1. **Live Signals Panel** — Current trade signal
s with color coding\\n   - Green = BUY YES\\n   - Red = BUY NO\\n   - Grey = HOL
D\\n\\n2. **Market Edge Scanner** — Top 10 markets by edge magnitude\\n\\n3. **P
&L Tracker** — Running P&L, win rate, trade count\\n\\n4. **Strategy Health** — 
Status of each strategy (OK / ERROR / NO_DATA)\\n\\n5. **Run Pipeline Button** —
Manually trigger signal generation\\n\\n### Auto-Refresh\\n\\nThe dashboard poll
s the API every 60 seconds. To disable:\\n```javascript\\n// In browser console\
\nclearInterval(autoRefreshInterval)\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## API Endpoints\\n\\n|
Endpoint | Method | Description |\\n|----------|--------|-------------|\\n| `/ap
i/signals` | GET | All trade signals |\\n| `/api/signals/latest` | GET | Most re
cent signal |\\n| `/api/markets` | GET | All markets analyzed |\\n| `/api/status
` | GET | System health status |\\n| `/api/run` | POST | Trigger live runner |\\
n| `/health` | GET | Health check |\\n\\n### Example API Calls\\n\\n```bash\\n# 
Get signals\\ncurl http://localhost:3200/api/signals\\n\\n# Get system status\\n
curl http://localhost:3200/api/status\\n\\n# Trigger pipeline run\\ncurl -X POST
http://localhost:3200/api/run\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Deployment Notes\\n\\n### L
ocal Development\\n\\n```bash\\n# Start all services\\nnode dashboard_api.js &  
Trading pipeline\\n```\\n\\n### Production Deployment\\n\\n1. **Set up Kalshi AP
I credentials**\\n   - Register at https://kalshi.com\\n   - Complete KYC verifi
cation\\n   - Generate production API key\\n   - Set `KALSHI_API_KEY` and `KALSH
I_DEMO=false`\\n\\n2. **Configure secrets management**\\n   ```bash\\n   # Optio
n 1: Environment variables (simple)\\n   export KALSHI_API_KEY=\\"...\\"\\n   \\
n   # Option 2: AWS Secrets Manager (recommended)\\n   aws secretsmanager get-se
cret-value --secret-id kalshi/api-key\\n   \\n   # Option 3: HashiCorp Vault\\n 
 vault kv get secret/kalshi/api-key\\n   ```\\n\\n3. **Database setup**\\n   ```
bash\\n   # Run migrations\\n   psql -f db/schema.sql\\n   psql -f db/schema_str
ategies.sql\\n   ```\\n\\n4. **Start services**\\n   ```bash\\n   # Using PM2\\n
  pm2 start dashboard_api.js --name dashboard\\n   pm2 start strategies/live_run
ner.js --name trader -- --execute\\n   \\n   # Or Docker\\n   docker-compose up 
